# Design System - Tahoe Glass Aesthetic

## Core Design Principles

Follow the macOS Tahoe 26 design language with liquid glass as the signature style.

**Using Tailwind CSS 4** - Modern utility-first CSS framework with improved performance and DX.

### Visual Hierarchy

- **Primary**: Clean, uncluttered interfaces
- **Secondary**: Consistent visual language
- **Tertiary**: Accessible and performant

### Color Palette

```css
/* Primary Tahoe Glass Colors */
--glass-bg: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
--glass-border: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
--glass-hover: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
--glass-focus: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.3);
```

## Component Styling Patterns

### Standard Glass Container

```tsx
className =
  "bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-md border border-white/20 rounded-xl shadow-lg p-6";
```

### Interactive Elements

```tsx
className =
  "hover:bg-white/20 transition-all duration-200 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-400/20";
```

### Form Elements

```tsx
className =
  "bg-white/5 border-white/10 rounded-lg px-4 py-2 focus:border-blue-400 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-400/20";
```

### Button Variants

```tsx
// Primary Button
className =
  "bg-blue-500/20 hover:bg-blue-500/30 border border-blue-400/30 text-blue-100 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg transition-all duration-200";

// Secondary Button
className =
  "bg-white/10 hover:bg-white/20 border border-white/20 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-lg transition-all duration-200";
```

## Typography Standards

- Use system fonts for native feel
- Maintain proper contrast ratios (WCAG AA)
- Use semantic heading hierarchy
- Implement responsive typography

## Spacing & Layout

- Use Tailwind's spacing scale consistently
- Implement proper grid layouts
- Use flexbox for component alignment
- Maintain consistent padding/margins

## Animation Guidelines

- Use subtle, natural transitions
- Keep animations under 300ms
- Use easing functions for smooth motion
- Avoid excessive animation on mobile

## Accessibility Requirements

- Implement proper ARIA labels
- Ensure keyboard navigation
- Maintain color contrast ratios (WCAG AA minimum)
- Test with screen readers

## Responsive Design

- Mobile-first approach with Tailwind breakpoints
- Use Tailwind's responsive utilities: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`, `2xl:`
- Test across devices with browser dev tools
- Ensure touch targets are at least 44x44px on mobile
